# Title: Firewall Disabled via Netsh.EXE
# Author: Fatih Sirin
# Date: 2019-11-01
# Level: medium
# Description: Detects netsh commands that turns off the Windows firewall
# MITRE Tactic: Uncategorized
# Tags: attack.defense-impairment, attack.t1686.003, attack.s0108
# Reference: https://github.com/SigmaHQ/sigma/blob/master/rules/windows/process_creation/proc_creation_win_netsh_fw_disable.yml
# False Positives:
#   - Legitimate administration activity

Image="*\\netsh.exe" OR OriginalFileName="netsh.exe" (CommandLine="*firewall*" CommandLine="*set*" CommandLine="*opmode*" CommandLine="*disable*") OR (CommandLine="*advfirewall*" CommandLine="*set*" CommandLine="*state*" CommandLine="*off*")